N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 192.4 - Records

State Regulations

Any establishment, as defined in this Part, that sells, offers for sale or distributes any onions or potatoes not produced in New York

State shall compile, maintain and make available for inspection, for a period
of two years, records of the disposal of culls or waste piles on a form or
forms prescribed by the commissioner. Notes
